Execute only PHASE 09.3.

Goal:
Implement queue worker system with Redis-ready backend, in-memory fallback, tenant context, task lifecycle, safe task execution, and worker APIs.

Create/update:
backend/app/workers/__init__.py
backend/app/workers/models.py
backend/app/workers/queue.py
backend/app/workers/worker_service.py
backend/app/workers/tasks.py
backend/app/workers/runner.py
backend/app/api/workers.py

Update:
backend/app/core/config.py
backend/app/core/events.py
backend/app/db/models.py
backend/app/db/repositories.py
backend/app/main.py
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.prod.yml
.env.example

Tests:
backend/app/tests/test_worker_queue.py
backend/app/tests/test_worker_tasks.py
backend/app/tests/test_phase9_api.py

Config:
WORKER_ENABLED=true
WORKER_QUEUE_BACKEND=redis
WORKER_CONCURRENCY=2
WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS=2
WORKER_TASK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=300
WORKER_MAX_RETRIES=3

Task types:
trading_scan
risk_check
backtest_run
optimization_run
content_pipeline_run
content_publish_dry_run
iot_status_check
notification_dispatch
audit_compaction
backup_run
custom

WorkerTask fields:
id
organization_id
workspace_id
task_type
status
payload
result
error
priority
attempts
max_retries
scheduled_at
started_at
finished_at
created_at
updated_at

WorkerStatus fields:
worker_id
hostname
status
current_task_id
processed_count
failed_count
last_heartbeat_at

Task statuses:
queued
running
completed
failed
retrying
cancelled

Queue methods:
enqueue(task_type, payload, tenant_context, priority=5) -> WorkerTask
dequeue(worker_id) -> WorkerTask | None
complete(task_id, result) -> WorkerTask
fail(task_id, error) -> WorkerTask
retry(task_id) -> WorkerTask
cancel(task_id) -> WorkerTask
list_tasks(filters) -> list[WorkerTask]

Worker behavior:
- Never crash entire worker on task failure.
- Capture result/error.
- Respect tenant context.
- Respect Guardian risk checks.
- Respect content approval checks.
- Respect IoT dry-run rules.
- Respect social dry-run rules.
- Redis-backed queue when Redis available.
- In-memory queue fallback in development.

APIs:
GET  /api/workers/status
GET  /api/workers/tasks
POST /api/workers/tasks
POST /api/workers/tasks/{task_id}/cancel
POST /api/workers/tasks/{task_id}/retry
GET  /api/workers/tasks/{task_id}

Rules:
- All routes require auth.
- Tenant scoped.
- Enqueue requires permission based on task type.
- Audit task enqueue/cancel/retry.

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

